Hello Serhat, The logs will not collect any confidential information, it should only use the id's of the machines and licenses. Indeed, the query should solve this issue, as it did on our test and for other other customers where this issue

 

Hello Serhat,

The logs will not collect any confidential information, it should only use the id's of the machines and licenses. 

Indeed, the query should solve this issue, as it did on our test and for other other customers where this issue also reproduced.
In our attempts to reproduce this issue, we usually had a few days as a time difference between the computers which are actually licensed and the ones which do not have a license assigned but they appear as licensed.
So we would like to collect the logs from your environment since on your server we could find computers without licenses which appear as licensed on the egde date. So we want to make sure that the license release is working as intended.

Let me know if we can have a 10 min session today at 15:00 NL time today in order to enable the logs.

Thank you,
Emil

It is not a change that we do for this server in particular, we are just going to update the license status for the computers which do not have a license assigned and they still appear as licensed.
